<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.development.js"></script>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.development.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@babel/standalone/babel.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id = "app"></div>
        <script src="text/babel">
         const element = <h1 className="a">Hello JSX!</h1>
         const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('app'))
         root.render(element)
        </script>
</body>
</html>
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.development.js"></script>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.development.js"></script>
    <script src="https://unpkg.com/@babel/standalone/babel.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id = "app"></div>
        <script src="text/babel">
         const element = <h1 className="a">Hello JSX!</h1>
         const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('app'))
         root.render(element)
        </script>
</body>
</html>
Syntax:
React.createElement(type,prop)
-type = tag name(div ,h1, p)
Props = className , id , onClick
To display the element
ReactDOM.createRoot()
ReactDOM.render() – to display the element.

Intro to JSX:
(Javascript XML) is a syntax extension for js , in react js , it allows us to write html code in react.

JSX: jsx code gets compiled into js 
Babel: a tool converts translates into js
Keypoints:
 <div id = "app"></div>
        <script src="text/babel">
         const element = <h1 className="a">Hello JSX!</h1>
         const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('app'))
         root.render(element)
        </script>

Without jsx ;-
 <div id = "app"></div>
        <script>
         const element =React.createElement(‘h1’, {className:"a"},Hello JSX)</h1>
         const root=ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('app'))
         root.render(element)
        </script>

Using function call:
You can call function call directly within jsx expressions
<div id=”a”></div>
<script type=”text/babel”>
Function getGreeting(name){
Return `Hello,${name}!Welcome to React`
}

